description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learning and Development Officer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£19,737 - £21,142 Per Annum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 Hours Per Week &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;About us&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at George Eliot our vision to &lt;em&gt;‘&lt;strong&gt;excel at patient care’&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; takes centre stage. An ever evolving clinically-led acute service provider we are on a journey to continually provide high quality, safe and responsive services delivered by inspiring, friendly and compassionate staff who share our corporate values which underpin everything we do. Our values are not just words on a piece of paper, they bond us together, reflect our ambition and shape who we are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;ffective Open Communication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;e&lt;strong&gt;x&lt;/strong&gt;cellence and safety in everything we do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt;hallenge but support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;xpect respect and dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L&lt;/strong&gt;ocal health that inspires confidence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Role&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting for two Learning and Development Officers to join our growing Learning and Development team. As an L&amp;D Officer for the Trust you will work as part of a dynamic team who support the whole breadth of administration and co-ordination of activities with the L&amp;D team. A significant part of this role will involve becoming subject matter experts in the use of our HR/ L&amp;D systems as this skill will be crucial to in order to effectively co-ordinate the wide range of courses and learning that takes place, and report effectively on this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a very varied role with a standard day in this role likely to involve you providing project support and administrative assistance for Apprenticeships, Core Skills and Essential Skills Training Framework, Appraisals, staff corporate induction, external training courses, career development activities, the Health and Wellbeing agenda and more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Learning and Development Team, we are keen to ensure that the development of our workforce is at the heart of everything we do, we are therefore willing to offer this role as a trainee opportunity for a candidate who is able to demonstrate that they meet the behavioural requirements that we are looking for if they are not yet holding the relevant qualifications. If a role is offered on this basis, it will be on a trainee contract, paid in line with Annex 21 of Agenda for Change until the applicant has undertaken the required programme of development for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For Further information please contact Sarah Newton (Apprenticeship and Work Experience Manager) on 07468744463.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Benefits &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our benefits include but are not limited to: On-site nursery, 27 days minimum annual leave plus 8 bank holidays, cycle to work scheme, flexible working, on-site discounted gym, extensive in-house course learning directory, buying and selling of annual leave, subsidised restaurant, tranquillity garden and generous subsidised on-site parking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 6th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post may close early due to high numbers of applications &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;so you are advised to apply promptly.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All correspondence for this vacancy will be sent by email; please check your account regularly including your Junk and SPAM areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;A great and friendly place to work, so bring your passion, commitment and expertise &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;and enjoy the opportunities to make a difference every day. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;#JoinTeamEliot&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Newton, Apprenticeship and Work Experience Manager, sarah.newton@geh.nhs.uk; 07468 744463&lt;/p&gt;
